Criteo services disabled on the browser you are currently using
Default settings of the browser you are currently using limit the use of third-party cookies as well as our capability to easily know if you have decided to disable Criteo Services. To make sure that Criteo services are disabled in the browser you are currently using, please click on the button below.
You have successfully disabled Criteo services.
Your data, your choice
To withdraw your consent to all Criteo services simply click on the button below:
Disable Criteo services
What will change?
Disable Criteo services will result in:
The deletion of the cookies dropped by Criteo in your browser you are currently using that allows us:
to recognize your browser or device;
and to link to you the data we have at our disposal.
The termination of the collection of your personal data for processing activities based on your consent.
The termination of the display of ads by Criteo, based on your consent, on the browser you are currently using.
Please note that Criteo can continue to process your personal data collected before you disabled Criteo services on the basis of Criteo’s legitimate interest.
To learn more about the personal data processed by Criteo go to
How we use your data
. To exercise your other rights, go to
Understand my rights
.
Please note that disabling Criteo services does not prevent ads from being displayed by other industry players. If you want to quickly and easily withdraw your consent to interest-based advertising from a range of industry players, including Criteo, we invite you to use the platforms provided by the following self-regulatory organizations:
Network Advertising Initiative’s platform
and/or
Digital Advertising Alliance’s platform
if you live in US.
Criteo may use hashed e-mails to provide tailored advertising by combining a hashed e-mail with another identifier. If you do not want your information linked to your hashed e-mail address, you may opt out through the
Network Advertising Initiative’s Audience-Matched Opt-Out Tool
.
IAB Europe’s platform (
YourOnlinechoices
) if you live within the EU.
If you wish to extend your choice to other browsers or to other devices, we invite you to repeat the operation from each of them. To facilitate this operation, you can:
Copy the following URL and paste it into another browser to extend your choice to it:
https://www.criteo.com/privacy/disable-criteo-services-on-internet-browsers/
Or flash the following QR code with a device and open the link to which it refers with another browser to extend your choice to it:
When it will change?
Criteo will stop displaying ads as soon as possible and at the latest after a maximum period of 24 hours.
Please note that it may take up to five weeks to process your request on Facebook as it is a separate environment over which we have no control. If you wish to immediately stop displaying our ads on your Facebook account, we invite you to modify the settings by clicking here:
Facebook settings
.
Is the change permanent?
Your choice will be saved in a dedicated cookie stored in your browser. This allows us to ensure the technical preservation of your choice by minimizing the impact on your privacy since no information will be stored in our systems on this subject. If you delete this cookie or update your device’s operating system, we may no longer be able to remember your choice. In which case, we invite you to simply repeat the operation.
Please also note that some mobile applications may use or rely on a technical feature called “webview” that allows app developer’s to display web applications or web pages directly in their application without leaving the application to open your usual browser. A webview can be independent both of your usual browser and the mobile application environment. Therefore we would recommend to withdraw consent also for this specific environment if you do not want to be served with Criteo advertisements.
Your data, your choice
Please note that the settings of your Safari browser may limit our technical ability to allow you to withdraw your consent to Criteo services, exercise your right to be forgotten and your right to object to the processing that Criteo may make of your personal data. Criteo offers several alternatives to you in order to provide you with the same control tools as those we provide to the users of other browsers. Opting out on other browsers only takes one click.
ALTERNATIVE N°1: Change settings and disable Criteo
1.Change browser settings for Criteo to be able to know and respect your choice on all websites.
Open Settings app
Select Safari
Switch Off “Prevent Cross-Site Tracking”
2. Come back to this page after changing your settings.
3. Disable Criteo services here.
Disable Criteo services
4. Force Safari App to close
If you need instructions on how to force an app to close, you can read more on:
Apple Support’s instructions
What will change?
Such a configuration of your smartphone will result in:
The deletion of the identifier stored in the browser you are currently using that allows us:
to recognize your browser or device;
and to link to you the data we have at our disposal.
The termination of the collection of your personal data.
And the termination of the display of ads by Criteo on the browser you are currently using.
Please note it does not prevent ads from being displayed by other industry players. If you want to quickly and easily withdraw your consent to interest-based advertising from a range of industry players, including Criteo, we invite you to use the platforms provided by the following self-regulatory organizations:
Network Advertising Initiative’s platform
and/or
Digital Advertising Alliance’s platform
if you live in US.
