Facebook settings
.
Is the change permanent?
Your choice will be saved in a dedicated cookie stored in your browser. This allows us to ensure the technical preservation of your choice by minimizing the impact on your privacy since no information will be stored in our systems on this subject. If you delete this cookie or update your device’s operating system, we may no longer be able to remember your choice. In which case, we invite you to simply repeat the operation.
ALTERNATIVE N°2: Install a content-blocking app to block personalized advertising from Criteo and others
Download
Disconnect.me
Change browser settings
Open Settings app
Select Safari
Select “Content Blockers”
Switch On “Privacy”
What will change?
Such a configuration of your smartphone will result in:
The termination of the collection of your personal data.
And the termination of the display of ads by Criteo when you are browsing from your web browser installed on the smartphone you are using.
Please note it might not prevent ads from being displayed by other industry players.
If you wish to extend your choice to other browsers installed on this device or to other devices, we invite you to repeat the operation from each of them. To facilitate this operation, you can:
Copy the following URL and paste it into another browser to extend your choice to it:
https://www.criteo.com/privacy/disable-criteo-services-on-internet-browsers/
Or flash the following QR code with a device and open the link to which it refers with another browser to extend your choice to it:
When it will change?
Criteo will stop displaying ads as soon as possible and at the latest after a maximum period of 24 hours.
Please note that it may take up to five weeks to process your request on Facebook as it is a separate environment over which we have no control. If you wish to immediately stop displaying our ads on your Facebook account, we invite you to modify the settings by clicking here:
Facebook settings
.
Is the change permanent?
If you modify the settings of your device, or if you update your device’s operating system, we may no longer be able to remember your choice. In which case, we invite you to simply repeat the operation.
Please also note that some mobile applications may use or rely on a technical feature called “webview” that allows app developer’s to display web applications or web pages directly in their application without leaving the application to open your usual browser. A webview can be independent both of your usual browser and the mobile application environment. Therefore we would recommend to opt out also from this specific environment if you do not want to be served with Criteo advertisements.
